{
  "text": "A formally comparable second pseudoautosomal region, Xq/ YqPAR, was discovered during the mapping of the X chromosome [CITATION_1] . It contains sequences that had been earlier recovered from both X and Y, and shows recombination over its entire extent [CITATION_2] . However, it also shows properties distinct from those of the Xp/YpPAR. The level of recombination is 6-fold higher than in the bulk of the X chromosome, though much less than the requisite recombination at every meiosis in the Xp/ YpPAR [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Perhaps more striking, when two genes were mapped to the Xq/YqPAR and studied further, IL9R showed the biallelic expression characteristic of Xp/YpPAR genes (7), but SYBL1 was found to be inactivated on both the inactive X and Y chromosomes, achieving dosage compensation in a unique manner [CITATION_5] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "23413222",
